                "institute": "1USALAS"
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Experiment performed using the Los",
                "Alamos National Laboratory solid-deuterium ultracold",
                "neutron source driven by an 800 MeV, 5 mA average",
                "proton beam provided by the Los Alamos Neutron",
                "Science Center linear accelerator"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Gamma rays from neutron radiative capture in",
                "hydrogen and vanadium were measured in a 100%",
                "efficient (relative to 3in x 3in NaI(Tl)) high purity",
                "germanium detector."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HE3SP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The neutron detector for the upscattering",
                "measurement was a 30 cm long drift tubes with 1.8 bar",
                "of 3He and 1 bar of CF4."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Absorption and scattering were measured for both",
                "samples. Ratios between vanadium and hydrogen count",
                "rates scattering and absorption were formed, from",
                "which cross section ratio absorption/scattering can",
                "be deduced for each element separately."
              ]
            }
          ],
